China Gives Tanzania Loan for $1 Billion Pipeline, Guardian Says

-- B y   D a v i d   M a l i n g h a   D o y a
-- 
2011-09-18T13:45:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-18/china-gives-tanzania-loan-for-1-billion-pipeline-guardian-says.html
China is set to sign an agreement
next week to grant Tanzania a loan to build a $1 billion  gas
pipeline  in the East African nation, the  Guardian on Sunday 
reported, citing Energy Minister William Ngeleja.  A local unit of Chinese National Petroleum Corp. and
Tanzania Petroleum Development Corp. will construct the pipeline
from Mtwara on the southern coastline to  Dar es Salaam , the
commercial capital, the newspaper reported, without saying who
told it that these companies will do the work.  To contact the reporter on this story:
David Malingha Doya in Dar es Salaam at 
 dmalingha@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Emily Bowers at 
 ebowers1@bloomberg.net  